HEADWORD: Cracowes
<hw>Cra"cowes</hw> <pr>(kr?"k?z)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <def>Long-toed
boots or shoes formerly worn in many parts of Europe; -- so called from
<etsep>Cracow</etsep>, in Poland, where they were first worn in the
fourteenth century.</def> <rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

